138098500.review:
Well, I finished ASTLIBRA Revision. On the timer 16.5 hours (Proton does not count playing time offline). In-game time is as follows: about 70 hours on "Normal" difficulty, and about 17 hours on "Hard" difficulty. Had to go through the game twice, as I wanted to collect all the achievements. It was two completely different experiences. On the subject of time, to confirm my words left only one word: [spoiler] "Geas" [/spoiler]. If you know, you know.

So, review. Saw a lot of good reviews of the game, decided to try it. I can say with confidence - it was one of the best gaming experiences.

What I liked:
-The story is strong, and it really is very good. The story leaves a nice aftertaste, it is completely finished and leaves no blank spots behind;
-Music accompaniment fits the game perfectly, the combination of multiple genres sets the pace of the game. It's a subjective feeling, but through the music you can somewhat predict which way the story might move;
-Various bosses, especially it feels that way on difficulty "Hard" and above;
-Was pleasantly surprised that some bosses can make a real bullet hell, it was a very pleasant experience since the days when I played Rabi-Ribi. It's not often you see a 2d side-scroller project with bullet hell mechanics;
-One of the best endgame content, with new mechanics and a big part of the story (no spoilers, it's just worth it);
-The game is well balanced on "Normal" difficulty, and some will find it challenging on "Hard". I can't speak for the other difficulties.
-Responsive controls, the character always does what you want to do;
-A lot of RPG mechanics, some mechanics show themselves very well in the endgame;
-Many options for enhancing a character's power, their combination makes the game very entertaining;
-Well-hidden secrets and puzzles that are fun to solve;
-The ability to quickly skip dialogues, which saved a lot of time on a second quick playthrough.

Neutral points:
-Although the secrets are hidden very well, there are some secrets that can be found either by accident or by digging every stone. Although I only had a few of these moments, [spoiler] the location where the Castlevania reference takes place is particularly memorable. [/spoiler]
-Maybe not everyone may like the graphics, but the game manages to pleasantly surprise with stunning views, especially in the second half of the game.

Controversial points:
-If you properly level up your character, the endgame part may be too easy for both "Normal" and "Hard". On the other hand, the balance of the endgame will depend entirely on the player.

I could not identify obvious disadvantages in the game. It completely fulfills its functions.

Bottom line: a great game, with good mechanics, bosses and a good story. ASTLIBRA Revision deserves to go into my box of awesome unique projects.

